


Threads in Java:
- A thread pool is a group of worker threads that are kept alive and reused.
- When a task is submitted:
- If a thread is free, it executes the task immediately.
- If all threads are busy, the task waits in a queue until a thread becomes available.
- After finishing, the thread returns to the pool instead of dying.


Thread Pool:
It's a collection of Threads, which are available to perform the submitted rasks.
Once task is completed, worker thread get back to thread pool and wait for new taks to assigned.
Thread can be re-used.

------------Async Annotations:
*Used to mark method that should run  asynchronously
Runs in a new Thread, without blocking the main thread.
@EnableAsync-----> main Spring Bott annotation class
When we mention that annotation, create async beans automatically
@Async----> The class

*** During Application startup, SB sees that no THreadPoolTaskExecutor bean present, so it creates it's default ThreadpooltaskExecutor with below configurations.
Default corePoolSize: 8

It's not recomment at all:
*Underutilization of Thread: Max pool and Queve pol ss more
High latency
Thread exhaustion
High memory usage


package SB.AOP;

import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RequestMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;

@RestController
@RequestMapping("/Threadapi")
public class ThreadController {
	
	@Autowired
	ThreadComponent comp;
	
	
	
	@GetMapping(path = "/gettt")
	 String getMeth() {
		System.out.println("Controller class Threads: "+ Thread.currentThread().getName());
		comp.tMeth();
		return "Thread";
		
	}

}





package SB.AOP;

import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Async;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;


@Component
@Async
public class ThreadComponent {
	
	 void tMeth() {
		System.out.println("ComponentClass Thread: "+ Thread.currentThread().getName());
	}

}







package SB.AOP;

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;
import org.springframework.context.ConfigurableApplicationContext;
import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableAsync;

@SpringBootApplication(exclude = {
        org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jdbc.DataSourceAutoConfiguration.class})
@EnableAsync
public class ThreadApp {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		
		ConfigurableApplicationContext context = SpringApplication.run(ThreadApp.class, args);
		context.getBean(ThreadComponent.class);

	}

}

